					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>158 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>400</height>
										<width>280</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>215</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p> 	158 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p> 	Too tight bound to determine exact gathering structure.  </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>The beginning of each pericope is marked in the margin by a large ornamental ס. </p>
									<p>Each pericope is divided into 7 sections numbered with Hebrew letters in colours in the margin. </p>
									<p>The numbers of the commandments are written in red ink in the margins. </p>
									<p>The masorah magna occupies two lines in the upper and three lines in the lower margin. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Yemenite square script, partially punctuated, of the 15th century. The scribe's name, <name type="person" role="scribe">Benayah ben Se῾adia ben Zekharyah ben Margaz</name>, is not mentioned in the colophon. On his identification see <ref target="Ettinghausen_1955" type="page">33</ref>. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Ibrahim ibn Yusuf ibn Sa῾id ibn Ibrahim al-Israili</name>(Hebrew version of his name in Or 2211): inscribed with his name in the colophon, Sana, 1469 (154v-155r).  </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yosef ben Suliman/Solomon</name>: inscribed with his name in two purchase notes (37v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Benyamin ben Avraham</name>: inscribed with his name in two purchase notes (37v). </p>
							<p>Avraham ben Yosef ben Sa῾id Hanatsel owner: inscribed with his name in a purchase note, Adar .. .. [year is deleted] according to the Seleucid era (38r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Sala'am ben Yosef ben Avraham</name>: inscribed with his name in a purchase note, Adar .. .. [year is deleted] according to the Seleucid era (38r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Ha-Kohen David ben Yosef</name>: inscribed with his name in a purchase note, Adar .. .. [year is deleted] according to the Seleucid era (38r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yosef ben Se῾adia</name>: inscribed with his name in a purchase note, Adar .. .. [year is deleted] according to the Seleucid era (38r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Avraham ben Yosef</name>: inscribed with his name in a purchase note, Adar .. .. [year is deleted] according to the Seleucid era (38r). </p>
							<p>Erased inscription in Hebrew characters (154). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yudah ben Se῾adia</name>.. ..: inscribed with his name in the margin (156v). </p>
							<p>Erased inscription with Hebrew characters (158v). </p>
						</additions>
